  <description><![CDATA[<p>Hotel Les Sherpas is a family run hotel that's located amongst the pine trees on the outskirts of the <a data-udi="umb://document/9e7d0f01e7964af0b7ee7c501cb0e893" href="/{localLink:umb://document/9e7d0f01e7964af0b7ee7c501cb0e893}" title="Courchevel">Courchevel 1850</a> village, and a five minute walk from the Jardin Alpin gondola giving you fantastic access to the beginners area. </p>
<h2>Relax and unwind</h2>
<p>The hotel's cosy saloon bar, with a log fireplace, is the perfect place for an après-ski drink. Unwind after a day on the slopes and head to the hotels spa area which features a heated indoor pool, sauna and steam room. Relax in the indoor pool and admire the view from the panoramic windows looking onto the snowy surroundings. You can also treat yourself to a massage or treatment to truly unwind after a day on the slopes.</p>
<h2>Great views</h2>
<p>As the hotel is tucked away in the corner of <a data-udi="umb://document/9e7d0f01e7964af0b7ee7c501cb0e893" href="/{localLink:umb://document/9e7d0f01e7964af0b7ee7c501cb0e893}" title="Courchevel">Courchevel</a>, you have incredible views from most areas of the hotel. Enjoy your meals with a panoramic mountain view through the large windows, which creates a bright dining area. The rooms are bright and comfortable, decorated in traditional Alpine décor and most of the rooms also have terraces or balconies so you can marvel at the stunning surroundings.</p>
<h2>Family friendly</h2>
<p>This hotel is perfect if you have children. Not only is 1850 perfect for those just learning or wanting to improve their confidence, the hotel also has a games room fully stocked with puzzles, board games and video games. Early dinner from 6.30pm is also a possibility, just let us know at the time of booking if you require this.</p>]]></description>
