  <roomsDescription><![CDATA[<p><strong>Snow Floor Rooms</strong> sleep two people and are around 23m². These rooms are located on the ground floor so will have a terrace area on the private snow front. Please note that these rooms are only accessible by stairs. </p>
<p><strong>Comfort Rooms</strong> sleep one to three people and are between 23-25m². These rooms are located on the first floor and have either a private terrace or balcony.</p>
<p><strong>Deluxe Rooms</strong> sleep one to three people and are approximately 25m². These rooms are located on the second or third floor of the hotel, and have a south or west facing  balcony.</p>
<p><span>Interconnecting rooms are made up of two double comfort or deluxe rooms creating a perfect family room. </span></p>
<p><strong>Room facilities</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>All rooms can be made up as twins or doubles (please specify when booking)</li>
<li>Private terrace or balcony</li>
<li>WC with a bath with a shower attachment </li>
<li>Free Wi-Fi</li>
<li>TV</li>
<li>Telephone</li>
<li>Safe</li>
<li>Hairdryer</li>
<li>Bathrobe and slippers</li>
</ul>]]></roomsDescription>
